text.__SUMMARY__:
Conus lobitensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.These snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans.
The species was named after Lobito Bay, Angola.
text.Distribution: This marine species occurs in the Atlantic Ocean off Angola.
